# Canonical site origin used by sitemap.xml, robots.txt, hreflang, and OG tags.
# Required in production — set it to the exact host visitors land on, including
# the www / non-www variant, with no trailing slash. If your DNS/host config
# 301s one variant to the other, this MUST be the destination, otherwise
# canonicals will point at the redirected variant and search engines will flag
# them. On Vercel, falls back to VERCEL_PROJECT_PRODUCTION_URL when omitted,
# which is fine only if no host-level redirect is in place.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://repertoire-scanner.example.com
